xxl.core.collections.bags.Bag

Packages that use Bag
xxl.core.collections.bags Contains some bags. 
xxl.core.collections.sweepAreas This package provides so-called SweepAreas. 
xxl.core.cursors.differences The package xxl.core.cursors.differences provides miscellaneous implementations of the difference operator on cursors. 
xxl.core.cursors.distincts The package xxl.core.cursors.distincts provides miscellaneous implementations of the distinct operator on cursors. 
xxl.core.cursors.groupers The package xxl.core.cursors.groupers provides miscellaneous implementations of the group operator on cursors. 
xxl.core.math.functions The package xxl.core.math.functions contains necessary classes and interfaces to work with real-valued functions. 
xxl.core.relational.cursors The package provides a whole algebra of cursors that extends the functionality of the classes cursors. 
 

Uses of Bag in xxl.core.collections.bags
 

Subinterfaces of Bag in xxl.core.collections.bags
 interface FIFOBag<E>
          The interface FIFO bag represents a FIFO (first in, first out) iteration over the elements of a bag.
 interface LIFOBag<E>
          The interface LIFO bag represents a LIFO (last in, first out) iteration over the elements of a bag.
 

Classes in xxl.core.collections.bags that implement Bag
 class AbstractBag<E>
          This class provides a skeletal implementation of the Bag interface, to minimize the effort required to implement this interface.
 class ArrayBag<E>
          This class provides an implementation of the Bag interface that internally uses an array with fixed size to store its elements.
 class ContainerBag
          This class provides an implementation of the Bag interface that internally uses a container to store its elements.
 class DecoratorBag<E>
          The class provides a decorator for a bag that follows the Decorator Design Pattern (for further details see Structural Patterns, Decorator in Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software by Erich Gamma, Richard Helm, Ralph Johnson, and John Vlissides).
 class DynamicArrayBag
          This class provides an implementation of the Bag interface that internally uses a resizable array to store its elements.
 class EmptyBag
          This class provides an empty bag.
 class ListBag<E>
          This class provides an implementation of the Bag interface that internally uses a list to store its elements.
 class UnmodifiableBag
          This class provides a decorator for a given bag that cannot be modified.
